-- Clinton Discharged From Hospital, State Department Says
-- B y   I n d i r a   A . R .   L a k s h m a n a n
-- 2013-01-02T23:30:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-02/clinton-discharged-from-hospital-state-department-says.html
Secretary of State Hillary Clinton
was discharged from New York-Presbyterian Hospital this evening
and her medical team is confident she will make a full recovery,
according to the State Department.  “She’s eager to get back to the office and we will keep
you updated on her schedule as it becomes clearer in the coming
days,” Deputy Assistant Secretary of State Philippe Reines said
in an e-mailed statement today.  Her medical team advised that she is “making good progress
on all fronts, and they are confident she will make a full
recovery,” Reines said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
